Plenty of storage for clothes.The rooms were very clean and best of all very quiet - there was no noise from above, the street or the hallway - the room doors are recessed slightly and this may have helped.	The hotel is lovely - shares one (or more) of it's walls with Notre Dame cathedral, yet is very contemporary, solid (read as "thick" walls so we found it very quiet!)	My only issue would be that we were on the first floor facing the street so our room was a bit noisy and we couldnt not open our curtains.	Our room faced St. Paul Street, which tended to be very quiet from 9 p.m. on and then into mid-morning.